\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 SynthDesc
\f1\b0\fs18 			
\f0\b\fs24 description of a synth definition\

\f2\b0 \
\
contains information about a SynthDef, such as its name, its control names and default values.\
also information is provided of its outputs and inputs and whether it has a gate control.\
\
SynthDescs are created by SynthDescLib, by reading a compiled synth def file.
\f1\fs18 \
\
	\cf2 SynthDescLib\cf0 .global.read(\cf3 "synthdefs/default.scsyndef"\cf0 );\
	\cf2 SynthDescLib\cf0 .global.synthDescs.at(\cf4 \\default\cf0 )\
\
\
\

\f0\b\fs24 	name
\f2\b0 			returns the name of the SynthDef\

\f0\b 	controlNames
\f2\b0 		returns an array of instances of ControlName, each of which \
					have the following fields: name, index, rate, defaultValue
\f1\fs18 \
	\
	\cf2 SynthDescLib\cf0 .global.synthDescs.at(\cf4 \\default\cf0 ).controlNames.postln\
	\
\
